  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.-step--1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.-step--1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.-step--1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.-step--1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.-step--1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dissolve half the <strong>green curry paste</strong>&nbsp;(save the rest for later) in 400ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped&nbsp;ginger,</strong>&nbsp;<strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> <strong>soy sauce sachets</strong> and stir to combine &ndash; this is your <strong>poaching liquid</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.-step--2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.-step--2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.-step--2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.-step--2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.-step--2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Place the <strong>coconut cream sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in a mug and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong> (this softens the naturally hard cream)</p>\r\n<p>Place your hand flat onto the <strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> thinner pieces</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/664.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pot with a matching lid over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>poaching liquid</strong>,<strong> chicken</strong> and enough <strong>boiled water</strong> to just cover the chicken</p>\r\n<p>Bring to the boil, cover with a lid&nbsp;and cook for 8-10 min or until the chicken is cooked through</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks&nbsp;and trim, then finely slice the<strong> spring onions</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
